.SH NAME
Element.scroll_event \- Element: scroll event
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]scroll\f[B]\f[R] event fires when an element has been
scrolled.
To detect when scrolling has completed, see the \f[CR]scrollend\f[R]
event of \f[CR]Element\f[R].
.SH SYNTAX
Use the event name in methods like \f[CR]addEventListener()\f[R], or set
an event handler property.
.IP
.EX
addEventListener(\(dqscroll\(dq, (event) => { })

onscroll = (event) => { }
.EE
.SH EVENT TYPE
A generic \f[CR]Event\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
The following examples show how to use the \f[CR]scroll\f[R] event with
an event listener and with the \f[CR]onscroll\f[R] event handler
property.
The \f[CR]setTimeout()\f[R] method is used to throttle the event handler
because \f[CR]scroll\f[R] events can fire at a high rate.
For additional examples that use \f[CR]requestAnimationFrame()\f[R], see
the \f[CR]Document\f[R] \f[CR]scroll\f[R] event page.
.SS Using \f[CR]scroll\f[R] with an event listener
The following example shows how to use the \f[CR]scroll\f[R] event to
detect when the user is scrolling inside an element:
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]div\f[R]
  id=\(dqscroll\-box\(dq
  style=\(dqoverflow: scroll; height: 100px; width: 100px; float: left;\(dq>
  <\f[B]p\f[R] style=\(dqheight: 200px; width: 200px;\(dq>Scroll me!</\f[B]p\f[R]>
</\f[B]div\f[R]>
<\f[B]p\f[R] style=\(dqtext\-align: center;\(dq id=\(dqoutput\(dq>Waiting on scroll events...</\f[B]p\f[R]>
.EE
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] element = document.querySelector(\(dqdiv#scroll\-box\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] output = document.querySelector(\(dqp#output\(dq);

element.addEventListener(\(dqscroll\(dq, (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  output.textContent = \(dqScroll event fired!\(dq;
  setTimeout(() \f[B]=>\f[R] {
    output.textContent = \(dqWaiting on scroll events...\(dq;
  }, 1000);
});
.EE
.SS Using \f[CR]onscroll\f[R] event handler property
The following example shows how to use the \f[CR]onscroll\f[R] event
handler property to detect when the user is scrolling:
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]div\f[R]
  id=\(dqscroll\-box\(dq
  style=\(dqoverflow: scroll; height: 100px; width: 100px; float: left;\(dq>
  <\f[B]p\f[R] style=\(dqheight: 200px; width: 200px;\(dq>Scroll me!</\f[B]p\f[R]>
</\f[B]div\f[R]>
<\f[B]p\f[R] id=\(dqoutput\(dq style=\(dqtext\-align: center;\(dq>Waiting on scroll events...</\f[B]p\f[R]>
.EE
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] element = document.querySelector(\(dqdiv#scroll\-box\(dq);
